Public Health

Environmental factors play a crucial role in public health, influencing the spread of diseases and overall well-being.

Key Environmental Health Issues:

  • Air pollution and respiratory diseases
  • Water contamination and waterborne illnesses
  • Climate change impacts on health
  • Exposure to toxic substances
  • Vector-borne diseases affected by environmental changes

Importance:

Understanding the link between environment and health is crucial for:

  • Disease prevention
  • Health policy development
  • Urban planning and development
  • Occupational health and safety

Improving environmental conditions can significantly enhance public health outcomes and quality of life.

); } export default PublicHealth;
